<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB07924</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT REDUCING WAIT TIME FOR REQUESTS FOR AN ACTION OR SERVICE IN PHONE CALLS FOR SERVICE-ORIENTED OFFICES AND PRESCRIBING PENALTIES FOR VIOLATION THEREOF AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Prescribes a phone call protocol whereby callers shall be put on hold FOR NO MORE THAN TWO (2) MINUTES; Mandates the National Telecommunication Commission to issue the implementing rules and regulations.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “National Phone Call Protocol Act”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>CASTELO, WINSTON &quot;WINNIE&quot;</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-07-18</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Tambunting (000 2018-08-14)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON CIVIL SERVICE AND PROFESSIONAL REGULATION ON 2018-07-30</td></tr></table>